cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with game theory and optimization, which are the main topics of the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of population games and the smart grid example suggest that the paper could also fit in the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. The focus on efficient computation and the use of variational inequalities suggest that the paper could also fit in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the use of aggregative games and coupling constraints suggests that the paper could also fit in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
